<L>But speke to vs as vntrest and in repreue</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde she segh wher damyan</L>
<L N="2208">Satte in &thorn;e busshe and knele he bygan
<PB REF="00000295.tif" N="265"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="470"></L>
<L>And wi&thorn; her fynger signes made she</L>
<L>&THORN;at Damyan shuld clymbe vpon a tree</L>
<L>&THORN;at charged was wi&thorn; frwte and vp he went</L>
<L N="2212">For verreily he knewe al her entent</L>
<L>And euery signe &thorn;at she cou&thorn;e make</L>
<L>wel bette &thorn;an Ianuare her owne make</L>
<L>ffor in a lettre she had tolde him all</L>
<L N="2216">Of &thorn;is matere howe he worchen shall</L>
<L>And &thorn;us I lat hym sitte in &thorn;e pirry</L>
<L>&amp; Ianuare and Mayus regnyng ful mery</L>
<L>&para; Bri&yogh;t was &thorn;e day and blewe &thorn;e firmament</L>
<L N="2220">Phebus of gold doune ha&thorn; his stremes sent</L>
<L>To gladen euery floure wi&thorn; his warmnesse</L>
