<L>Pluto &thorn;at is &thorn;e kyng of ffairye</L>
<L N="2228">And mony a lady in his companye</L>
<L>ffolowinge his wiff &thorn;e qwene proserpina</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;at he rauyssshed out of proserpina</L>
<L>whilis &thorn;at she gadered floures in a mede</L>
<L N="2232">In Claudyan &yogh;e may &thorn;e stories rede</L>
<L>How in his Grisly carte he her fette</L>
<L>This kinge of fairye adoune hym sette</L>
<L>Vpon a benche of Turves fressh and grene</L>
<L N="2236">And ri&yogh;t anon seide he &thorn;us to his quene</L>
<L>My wif quod he &thorn;at may no wi&yogh;t say nay</L>
<L>The experience proueth it euery day</L>
<L>The treson which &thorn;at womman do&thorn; to man<MILESTONE N="127a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2240">x<SUP>c</SUP>. thousand telle I can</L>
<L>Notable of &yogh;oure vntrou&thorn;e and britelnesse</L>
<L>O salamon richest of alle rychesse</L>
<L>ffulfilled of sapience and of worldely glorie</L>
<L N="2244">fful wor&thorn;i bene &thorn;i wordes to memorie
<PB REF="00000296.tif" N="266"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="471"></L>
<L>To euery wight &thorn;at witte and reson can/</L>
<L>Thus preise&thorn; he &yogh;it &thorn;e bounte of man</L>
<L>Among a Ml men &yogh;it fonde I on</L>
<L N="2248">But of alle wommen fonde I neuere noon</L>
<L>Thus sei&thorn; &thorn;is knyght &thorn;at knowe&thorn; &yogh;oure wickednesse</L>
<L>And Ihesus filius C[i]rak as I gesse</L>
<L>Ne speke&thorn; of &yogh;ou but seelden reuerence</L>
<L N="2252">A wilde fuyr a corrupte pestilence</L>
<L>So falle vpon &yogh;oure bodies &yogh;it to ny&yogh;t</L>
<L>Ne Se &yogh;e not &thorn;is honurable knyght</L>
<L>By cause alas &thorn;at he is blynde and olde</L>
<L N="2256">His owne man shal make him kokewold</L>
<L>Lo where he sitte &thorn;e leccheour in &thorn;e tree</L>
<L>Nowe wil I graunte of my maieste</L>
<L>Vnto &thorn;is olde blynde wor&thorn;i kny&yogh;t</L>
<L N="2260">That he shal han a&yogh;ein his eyen si&yogh;t</L>
<L>whan &thorn;at his wiff wold do him vilanye</L>
<L>&thorn;an shal he knowe al her harlotrie</L>
<L>Boo&thorn; in repreef of hure and o&thorn;er moo/</L>
<L N="2264">&para; &YOGH;e Sire quod proserpyne and wil &yogh;e soo</L>
<L>Nowe by my moders sire soule I swere</L>
<L>&THORN;at I shal &yogh;euen hire suffisant answere</L>
<L>And alle wommen aftere for &yogh;oure sake</L>
<L N="2268">That &thorn;ou&yogh;e &thorn;ei bene in eny gilt ytake</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; face bolde &thorn;ei shullen hem self excuse</L>
<L>And beren hem doune &thorn;at wolden hem accuse</L>
<L>ffor lacke of answer noon of hem shul dyen</L>
<L N="2272">All hadde &yogh;e seie a &thorn;inge wi&thorn; bo&thorn; &yogh;oure yen</L>
<L>&YOGH;it shullen we so visage it hardely</L>
<L>And wepe and swere and chide subtily</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;e shullen bene as lewde as bene gees<MILESTONE N="127b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2276">what recketh me of such autoritees/</L>
<L>I wote wel &thorn;is Iwe this salomon</L>
<L>ffoonde of vs wymmen foles mony on</L>
<L>But &thorn;ou&yogh;e &thorn;at he ne fonde no good womman</L>
<L N="2280">&thorn;er ha&thorn; yfounde mony ano&thorn;er man
<PB REF="00000297.tif" N="267"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="472"></L>
<L>wommen ful trewe ful good ful vertuous</L>
<L>witnesse of hem &thorn;at dwellen in cristes hous</L>
<L>wi&thorn; martierdome &thorn;ei proued her constance</L>
<L N="2284">&thorn;e Romayn geestes maken remembraunce</L>
<L>Of mony a verrey trewe wif also /</L>
<L>But sir ne be not wro&thorn; as be it soo /</L>
<L>&thorn;ough &thorn;at he seide he foonde no good womman</L>
<L N="2288">I prei &yogh;ou take &thorn;e sentence of &thorn;e man</L>
<L>He ment &thorn;us &thorn;at in souereyn bounte</L>
<L>Nis noon but god but nei&thorn;ere he ne she</L>
<L>Eye for verrey god &thorn;at nys but oon</L>
<L N="2292">what make &yogh;e so moche of Salomon</L>
<L>what &thorn;ou&yogh;e he made a temple goddys hous</L>
<L>what &thorn;ou&yogh;e he were riche and glorious</L>
<L>So made he a temple of fals goddes ./</L>
<L N="2296">Who my&yogh;t do a &thorn;inge &thorn;at more forbode es</L>
<L>Parde as faire as &yogh;e his name enplastere</L>
<L>He was a lecchoure and an ydolastre</L>
<L>And in his elde he verrey god forsoke</L>
<L N="2300">And &yogh;if &thorn;at god nad as sei&thorn; &thorn;e booke</L>
<L>yspared him for his faders sake he sholde</L>
<L>haue lost his regne souner &thorn;an he wolde</L>
<L>I sette nou&yogh;t of alle &thorn;e vyleynye</L>
<L N="2304">&thorn;at &yogh;e of wommen write a botterflie</L>
<L>I am a womman nede mote I speke</L>
<L>Ei&thorn;er ellis swelle to myn hert breke</L>
<L>ffor si&thorn;en he seide &thorn;at we bene Iangler[ess]es</L>
<L N="2308">As euer mote I brouke bo&thorn; my tresses</L>
<L>I shal not spare for no curtesye</L>
<L>To speke him harme &thorn;at wold vs vilanye</L>
<L>Dame quod &thorn;is Pluto be no lenger wro&thorn;e<MILESTONE N="128a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2312">I &yogh;eue it vp but si&thorn;ens I swore myn o&thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;at I wolde graunten him his si&yogh;t a&yogh;eyn</L>
<L>My word shal stonde &thorn;at warne I &thorn;e certeyn</L>
<L>I am a kinge it sitte me not to lye</L>
<L N="2316">And I quod she a quene of fairye
<PB REF="00000298.tif" N="268"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="473"></L>
<L>Her Answere she shal haue I vndertake</L>
<L>Lat vs no moo wordes make</L>
<L>&para; fforso&thorn; I wil no lenger &yogh;ou contrarie</L>
<L N="2320">Now lat vs turne a&yogh;ein to Ianuarye</L>
<L>That in &thorn;is Gardyn wi&thorn; &thorn;is faire Maye</L>
<L>Synge&thorn; wel merier &thorn;an &thorn;e popeniay</L>
<L>&YOGH;ou loue I best and shal and o&thorn;er non</L>
<L N="2324">So longe aboute &thorn;e alaies is he gon</L>
<L>Till he was come a&yogh;einst &thorn;ilk piry</L>
<L>where as &thorn;is damyan sitte&thorn; ful mery</L>
<L>On hegh amonge &thorn;e fresshe leues grene</L>
<L N="2328">This fresshe May &thorn;at is so bri&yogh;t an shene</L>
<L>Gan forto sigh and seide alas my side</L>
<L>Now sire quod she for ou&yogh;te &thorn;at may bytide</L>
<L>I moost haue of &thorn;e peeres &thorn;at I see</L>
<L N="2332">Or I mote dye so soore longe&thorn; me</L>
<L>To eten of &thorn;e smale peres grene</L>
<L>Helpe for her loue &thorn;at is of heuene quene</L>
<L>I telle &yogh;ou wel a womman in my plite</L>
<L N="2336">May haue to fruete so grete an appetite</L>
<L>&THORN;at she may dyen but she it haue</L>
<L>Allas quod he &thorn;at I nad here a knaue</L>
<L>That cou&thorn;e clymbe alas alas quod he</L>
<L N="2340">ffor I am blinde &yogh;e sire no fors quod she</L>
<L>But wold &yogh;e vouchesauf for goddis sake</L>
<L>&thorn;e piry in wi&thorn; &yogh;oure armes forto take</L>
<L>ffor wel I wote &thorn;at &yogh;e mystrest me</L>
<L N="2344">Ellis shuld I clymbe wel ynowe quod she</L>
<L>So I my fote my&yogh;t sette vpon &yogh;oure bak</L>
<L>ffor so&thorn;e seide he in me shal be no lak</L>
<L>Might I &yogh;ou helpe wi&thorn; myn herte blood<MILESTONE N="128b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2348">He stoupe&thorn; doune and on his bak she stood</L>
<L>And cau&yogh;t hure by a twist and vp she goo&thorn;</L>
<L>Ladyes I preie &yogh;ou &thorn;at ye be nat wroo&thorn;</L>
<L>I can not glose I am a rude man</L>
<L N="2352">And sodeynly anoon &thorn;is damyan
<PB REF="00000299.tif" N="269"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="474"></L>
<L>Gan pullen vp &thorn;e smokke and in he &thorn;ronge</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;at Pluto segh &thorn;is grete wronge</L>
<L>To Ianuarie he &yogh;aue his si&yogh;t ageyn</L>
<L>[And made him se / as wel as evir he myht<MILESTONE UNIT="Addit. 5140 folio" N="167b"></L>
<L>And whan he hadde / cauht his syht ageyn<MILESTONE UNIT="Addit. 5140 folio" N="168a"><NOTE PLACE="marg">[<I>In Reg.</I> 17 <I>D xv</I>, <I>lf</I> 122, <I>bk, lf</I> 123;<I>not in Reg.</I> 18 <I>C</I>2, <I>leaf</I> 104.]</NOTE>]</L>
<L>ne was &thorn;er neuer man of &thorn;inge so feyn</L>
<L>But on his wiff his &thorn;ou&yogh;t was euermoo</L>
<L N="2360">Vp to &thorn;e tree he cast his eyen twoo /</L>
<L>And segh &thorn;at Damyan his wif had dressed.</L>
<L>In which manere it may not be expressed</L>
<L>But [&yogh;if] I wolde speke vncurteysly</L>
<L N="2364">And vp he &yogh;aue a roringe and a crye</L>
<L>As do&thorn;e &thorn;e modere whan &thorn;e childe shal dye</L>
<L>oute helpe alas harowe I gan to crye</L>
<L>O stronge lady stoor what doostowe</L>
<L N="2368">And she answere&thorn; sire what eileth &yogh;owe</L>
<L>Haue pacience and reson in &yogh;oure mynde</L>
<L>I haue &yogh;ou hulpen of bo&thorn; &yogh;oure eyen blynde</L>
<L>Vp perile of my soule I shal not lyen</L>
<L N="2372">As me was tau&yogh;te to hele wi&thorn; &yogh;oure eien</L>
<L>Was no &thorn;inge bette forto make &yogh;ou see</L>
<L>Than strogle wi&thorn; a man vpon a tree</L>
<L>God wote I did it in ful good entent</L>
<L N="2376">Stroggel quod he . &yogh;e algate in it went</L>
<L>God &yogh;eue &yogh;ou bo&thorn;e a shames de&thorn; to dyen</L>
<L>He swyued &thorn;e I segh it wi&thorn; myne eyen</L>
<L>And ellis be I honged by &thorn;e hals</L>
<L N="2380">Than is quod she &thorn;e medecyne fals</L>
<L>ffor certeynly if &yogh;e my&yogh;ten see</L>
<L>&YOGH;e wold not saye no wordes vnto me</L>
<L>&YOGH;e han some glymysing and no parfit si&yogh;t</L>
<L N="2384">I see quod he as wel as euere I my&yogh;t</L>
<L>Thonked be god wi&thorn; bo&thorn; myn eyen twoo<MILESTONE N="129a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And by my trou&thorn;e me &thorn;ought he did &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> soo</L>
<L>&YOGH;e mase mase good sir quod she</L>
<L N="2388">This &thorn;onk I haue for I haue made &yogh;ou see
<PB REF="00000300.tif" N="270"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="475"></L>
<L>Allas quod she &thorn;at euere I was so kinde</L>
<L>Now dame quod he lat al passe out of mynde</L>
<L>Come doune my leef and if I haue myssayd</L>
<L N="2392">God helpe me so as I am euel apayd</L>
<L>But by my faders soule I wend haue seyn</L>
<L>How &thorn;at &thorn;is Damyan had by &thorn;e leyn</L>
<L>And &thorn;at &thorn;i smok had leye vpon &thorn;i brest</L>
<L N="2396">&YOGH;e sir quod she &yogh;e may wene as &yogh;ou lest</L>
<L>But sir a man &thorn;at wake&thorn; out of sclepe</L>
<L>He may not sodeynly wel take kepe</L>
<L>Vpon a &thorn;inge ne seen it parfitely</L>
<L N="2400">To &thorn;at he be adawed verrely</L>
<L>Ri&yogh;t so a man &thorn;at Iong ha&thorn; blynde ybe</L>
<L>Ne may not sodeynly so wel yse</L>
<L>ffirst whan &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> si&yogh;t is newe commen ageyn</L>
<L N="2404">As he &thorn;at ha&thorn; a day or tweyen yseyn</L>
<L>Til &thorn;at &yogh;oure si&yogh;t ystabled be a while</L>
<L>Ther may ful mony a si&yogh;t &yogh;ou begile</L>
<L>Be&thorn; ware I preye &yogh;ou for by heuene kinge</L>
<L N="2408">fful mony a man wene&thorn; forto se a &thorn;inge</L>
<L>And it is al ano&thorn;er &thorn;an it seme&thorn;</L>
<L>He &thorn;at mysconceyue&thorn; mysdeme&thorn;</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at word she lepe doun fro &thorn;e tre</L>
<L N="2412">This Ianuarie who is glad but he</L>
<L>He clippe&thorn; hire and kisse&thorn; hure ful oft</L>
<L>And on hire wombe he stroke&thorn; hure ful soft</L>
<L>And to his Palays home he ha&thorn; hire lad</L>
<L N="2416">Nowe good men I prey &yogh;ou to be glad</L>
<L>Thus ende&thorn; here my tale of Ianuarie</L>
<L N="2418">God blesse vs and his modere seynt Marie</L>
</LG>
