<HEAD>GROUP <B>D.</B> FRAGMENT V.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; 1. WIFE OF BATH'S PREAMBLE.</HEAD>
<HEAD>PETWORTH MS.</HEAD>
<HEAD>And here bygynne&thorn; &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> prologe of &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> wif of Bathe <NOTE PLACE="head"><I>leaf</I> 129</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Experience thou&yogh;e noon autorite<MILESTONE N="129b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>were in &thorn;is world ri&yogh;t ynou&yogh;e for me</L>
<L>To speke of woo &thorn;at is in mariage</L>
<L N="4">ffor lordingges si&thorn; I twelue &yogh;ere was of age</L>
<L>Thonked be god &thorn;at is eterne alyue</L>
<L>Husbondes atte church door haue I had fyve</L>
<L>&YOGH;if I so often my&yogh;t han wedded be</L>
<L N="8">But alle were wor&thorn;i men in her degre</L>
<L>But me was tolde certeyn not longe agon is</L>
<L>That si&thorn;en crist ne went neuer but onys</L>
<L>To wedden in &thorn;e cane of galile</L>
<L N="12">&thorn;at by &thorn;ilk ensample tau&yogh;te he me</L>
<L>That I ne shuld wedded be but onys</L>
<L>Herk eek. loo such a sharpe word for &thorn;e nones</L>
<L>Beside a welle Ihesu god and man</L>
<L N="16">Spake in repreef of &thorn;e Samaritan</L>
<L>Thow hast yhad .v. husbondes quod he</L>
<L>And &thorn;at ilk man &thorn;at nou&yogh; ha&thorn; &thorn;e</L>
<L>Is not thyne husbond &thorn;us seide he certeyn</L>
<L N="20">What he ment &thorn;er-by I can not seyn</L>
<L>Wele; But &thorn;at I aske whi the fift man</L>
<L>Was non husbond to &thorn;e Samaritan</L>
<L>How mony my&yogh;t she han in mariage</L>
<L N="24">&YOGH;it herd I neuere telle in myn age
<PB REF="00000302.tif" N="272"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="335"></L>
<L>vpon &thorn;is nombre diffinicioun</L>
<L>Men may devise and glosen vp and doun</L>
<L>But wel I wote expresse wi&thorn;-outen lye</L>
<L N="28">God bad us forto wexe and multiplie</L>
<L>That ge[n]tile text can I wel vnderstond</L>
<L>Eke wel I wote he seide myn husbond<NOTE PLACE="marg">&para; Relinquet homo patrem &amp; matrem &amp; adherebit vxori sue &amp; cetera.</NOTE></L>
<L>Shuld lete fadere and modere and take to me</L>
<L N="32">But of no nombre mencion made he</L>
<L>Of bygamy or of octogamye</L>
<L>Whi shuld men &thorn;an of it han vilanye</L>
<L>loke here the wise man . kyng Salomon</L>
<L N="36">I trowe he had wyues moo &thorn;an &omacr;&omacr;n<NOTE PLACE="marg">&para; Genesis ij<SUP>o</SUP> quam-obrem</NOTE></L>
<L>Now wold god it lieful were to me<MILESTONE N="130a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>To be refresshed half so oft as he</L>
<L>Which &yogh;ift of god had he for all his wyues</L>
<L N="40">No man ha&thorn; such &thorn;at in &thorn;is world alyue es /</L>
<L>God wote &thorn;is noble kinge as to my witte</L>
<L>&thorn;e furst ny&yogh;t had mony a mery fitte</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; eche of hem so wel was hym alyve</L>
<L N="44">Blessed be god . &thorn;at I haue wedded fyve</L>
<L>Welcome &thorn;e .vi. whan &thorn;at euer he shal</L>
<L>ffor si&thorn; I wil not kepe me chaast in all</L>
<L>Whan myn husbond is fro &thorn;e world ygon</L>
<L N="48">Somme cristen man shal wedde me anon</L>
<L>ffor &thorn;an the apostel sei&thorn; &thorn;at I am fre</L>
<L>To wedde a goddes half where it like&thorn; me</L>
<L>He sei&thorn; &thorn;at to be wedded is no synne</L>
<L>Better is to be wedded &thorn;an to brenne<NOTE PLACE="marg">&para; Melius est nubere quam vri. //</NOTE></L>
<L N="53">What rekke&thorn; me &thorn;oo folk sey vylanye</L>
<L>Of shrewde lame&thorn;e and his Bygamye</L>
<L>I woot wel Abraham was an holy man</L>
<L N="56">And Iacob eke as fer as euer I can</L>
<L>And eche of hem had wyues moo &thorn;an twoo</L>
<L>And mony ano&thorn;er holy man also</L>
<L>Where can &yogh;e say in eny maner age</L>
<L N="60">That vs god defended mariage
<PB REF="00000303.tif" N="273"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="336"></L>
<L>By expresse woord I prei &yogh;ou telle&thorn; me</L>
<L>Or where commaunded he virginite</L>
<L>I wote as wel as &yogh;e it is no drede</L>
<L N="64">&thorn;e Apostel whan he speke&thorn; of maydenhede</L>
<L>He seide &thorn;erof precept had he non</L>
<L>Men may counsaile a womman to be on</L>
<L>But counseilling nys non comaundement</L>
